A capacitor and resistor are connected in parallel to an open switch and 12 V battery. Which of the following describes what will happen when the switch is closed initially:

choices.W: The spin orientation of the electron within the hydrogen atom have slightly different energy states, and the shift in the spin orientation gives rise to a photon with wavelength 21 cm.
choices.X: The electron of a hydrogen atom drops from the 2nd to the first energy state, emitting a photon of wavelength 21 cm.
